  "content": "=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\" style=\"color: var(--accent-green);\">The Reveal</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\"><span class=\"highlight-red\">Wayland</span> Again.</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\">Not a memory problem. A display server problem.</div>\n  <!-- Wayland vs X11 comparison - bigger -->\n  <div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 28px;\">\n    <div class=\"card\" style=\"border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-red); text-align: center; padding: 36px 28px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 48px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: var(--accent-red);\">✕</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 32px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-red); margin-bottom: 8px;\">Wayland</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 20px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.4;\">Display server broke GPU communication. Black playback, misleading errors.</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"card\" style=\"border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-green); text-align: center; padding: 36px 28px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 48px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: var(--accent-green);\">✓</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 32px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-green); margin-bottom: 8px;\">X11</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 20px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.4;\">Force X11 session. Full GPU access restored, everything works.</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Terminal fix -->\n  <div class=\"terminal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 24px; font-size: 18px;\">\n    <span class=\"comment\"># Force X11 instead of Wayland</span><br>\n    <span class=\"prompt\">$</span> <span class=\"cmd\">3 environment variables</span> <span class=\"highlight-val\">+ /opt/resolve/bin/resolve</span>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Stat -->\n  <div class=\"stat-box\" style=\"text-align: center; border: 2px solid rgba(16,185,129,0.3); background: rgba(16,185,129,0.06); padding: 36px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size: 56px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-green); margin-bottom: 4px;\">Full 4K Playback</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size: 22px; color: var(--text-secondary);\">No proxies needed. No workarounds. Just the right display server.</div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"insight-box\">\n    <p>Turns out it wasn't a memory problem. It was a Wayland compatibility issue.</p>\n  </div>",
